AWS seeks an Audit Analyst to perform audits, provide input to control design and report audit results to management. This candidate will provide consultative support to the CBS team to identify opportunities for control improvements with the objective of mitigating risk and improving operations and compliance in order to enhance the customer experience related to billing. In this capacity, you will dive deep into the scope of each audit to develop meaningful findings and help drive sustainable solutions. You will understand complex business processes and identify the full range of related compliance, organizational, and technology risks. You will demonstrate analytical skills, solid business judgement, and the capability to drive the right results with a collaborative and pragmatic approach. Additionally, you will participate in adhoc assignments on priority basis and as directed by Custom Billing leadership.
 
 Retrieve and analyze data using Excel, Salesforce, and other data management/BI systems 
 Support monthly billing processes between multiple external and internal AWS teams by auditing billing data, providing data management, and pricing calculations 
 Proactively identify and implement operational improvements, enhancements, and system customizations that meet business requirements 
 Support recurring and ad hoc reporting for various internal/external stakeholders 
 Accounting experience with accruals and receivables - Experience with financial contracts and comfortable with contractual language - Strong attention to detail and excellent problem solving skills - Track record for being detail-oriented with a demonstrated ability to self-motivate and follow-through on projects - Strong quantitative, analytical and organizational skills - Highly organized, have multi-tasking skills, and efficient in ambiguous situations 
 
